name: r-esquisse
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-esquisse
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/esquisse_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/esquisse/esquisse_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 41a637214f0fcff8f1d40cfde7a26a06aa18f4b7a2b5c5e95c3387520cdd325f

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-datamods
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-scales
    - r-shiny >=1.1.0
    - r-shinywidgets >=0.6.0
    - r-styler
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-datamods
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-scales
    - r-shiny >=1.1.0
    - r-shinywidgets >=0.6.0
    - r-styler

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('esquisse')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('esquisse')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/dreamRs/esquisse
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: A 'shiny' gadget to create 'ggplot2' charts interactively with drag-and-drop to map your variables. You can quickly visualize your data accordingly to their type, export to 'PNG' or 'PowerPoint', and retrieve the code to reproduce the chart.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
